paragraphs.title: Visualize Vehicle Data in Tabular Format
Feature Engineering #1 - ReSampling Time Series
paragraphs.text:
import com.hortonworks.scythe._
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat
import com.hortonworks.scythe.functions._
import java.util.Calendar;
import org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import java.sql.{ Date, Timestamp }

def formatStr(rate: String) : String = {
    rate match {
      case "Y" =>  "yyyy"
      case "Month" =>  "yyyy-MM"
      case "D" => "yyyy-MM-dd"
      case "H" => "yyyy-MM-dd HH"
      case "M" => "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm"
      case "S" => "yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss"
    }
}

val c = date_format(df0("time"), formatStr("D"))  

val format = List(IntegerType, DoubleType).contains(df0.schema("time").dataType)
val ds1 = format match {
  case true => df0.withColumnRenamed("time", "time_bin")
  case false => df0.withColumn("time_bin", c)
}

ds1.createOrReplaceTempView("ds1")
val ds2 = spark.sql(s"""
select time_bin,last_value(year) as year,last_value(make) as make,last_value(model) as model, last_value(weather_temp) as weather_temp,
last_value (engine_temp) as engine_temp ,last_value(speed_mph) as speed_mph ,last_value(rpm) as rpm, last_value (driver) as driver, last_value(state) as state,
last_value(last_service_dt) as last_service_dt,last_value(miles_at_lst_service) as miles_at_lst_service, last_value(miles_current) as miles_current,
last_value(miles_since_lst_service) as miles_since_lst_service, last_value(failure) as failure, last_value(miles_since_last_bin) as miles_since_last_bin
from ds1 group by time_bin,driver order by time_bin """)
ds2.createOrReplaceTempView("ds2")

paragraphs.title: Vehicle Make and Models in the Fleet
Feature Engineering #2 - Categorical Values - OneHotEncoding to the Rescue
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row
import org.apache.spark.mllib.regression.LabeledPoint
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.ProbabilisticClassifier
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.LogisticRegression
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.MulticlassMetrics
import org.apache.spark.mllib.util.MLUtils
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler
import org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.Vectors
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import org.apache.spark.mllib.evaluation.BinaryClassificationMetrics
import org.apache.spark.mllib.classification.LogisticRegressionWithLBFGS
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.{BinaryLogisticRegressionSummary, LogisticRegression}
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.{OneHotEncoder, StringIndexer}


//Index and Encode driver, make, model, state

// Model
val indexer_model = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("model").setOutputCol("modelIndex").fit(df0)
val indexed_model = indexer_model.transform(df0)
val encoder_model = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("modelIndex").setOutputCol("modelVec")
val encoded_model = encoder_model.transform(indexed_model)

// Make
val indexer_make = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("make").setOutputCol("makeIndex").fit(encoded_model)
val indexed_make = indexer_make.transform(encoded_model)
val encoder_make = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("makeIndex").setOutputCol("makeVec")
val encoded_make = encoder_make.transform(indexed_make)

// Driver
val indexer_driver = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("driver").setOutputCol("driverIndex").fit(encoded_make)
val indexed_driver = indexer_driver.transform(encoded_make)
val encoder_driver = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("driverIndex").setOutputCol("driverVec")
val encoded_driver = encoder_driver.transform(indexed_driver)

// State
val indexer_state = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("state").setOutputCol("stateIndex").fit(encoded_driver)
val indexed_state = indexer_state.transform(encoded_driver)
val encoder_state = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("stateIndex").setOutputCol("stateVec")
val encoded_state = encoder_state.transform(indexed_state)

val encodedCols = encoded_state

encodedCols.show
encodedCols.printSchema


// create feature vector
val assembler =  new VectorAssembler()
  .setInputCols(Array("year","makeVec","modelVec","weather_temp","engine_temp","speed_mph","rpm","driverVec","stateVec","miles_at_lst_service","miles_current"))
  .setOutputCol("features")
  
// assemble a new vector from dataframe
// assemble a new vector from dataframe

val df1 = assembler.transform(encodedCols).select($"failure".cast(DoubleType).as("label"), $"features")



// Model
val indexer_model = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("model").setOutputCol("modelIndex").fit(ds2)
val indexed_model = indexer_model.transform(ds2)
val encoder_model = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("modelIndex").setOutputCol("modelVec")
val encoded_model = encoder_model.transform(indexed_model)

// Make
val indexer_make = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("make").setOutputCol("makeIndex").fit(encoded_model)
val indexed_make = indexer_make.transform(encoded_model)
val encoder_make = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("makeIndex").setOutputCol("makeVec")
val encoded_make = encoder_make.transform(indexed_make)

// Driver
val indexer_driver = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("driver").setOutputCol("driverIndex").fit(encoded_make)
val indexed_driver = indexer_driver.transform(encoded_make)
val encoder_driver = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("driverIndex").setOutputCol("driverVec")
val encoded_driver = encoder_driver.transform(indexed_driver)

// State
val indexer_state = new StringIndexer().setInputCol("state").setOutputCol("stateIndex").fit(encoded_driver)
val indexed_state = indexer_state.transform(encoded_driver)
val encoder_state = new OneHotEncoder().setInputCol("stateIndex").setOutputCol("stateVec")
val encoded_state = encoder_state.transform(indexed_state)

val encodedCols = encoded_state

encodedCols.show
encodedCols.printSchema


// create feature vector

  .setInputCols(Array("year","makeVec","modelVec","weather_temp","engine_temp","speed_mph","rpm","driverVec","stateVec","miles_at_lst_service","miles_current"))
  .setOutputCol("features")
  
// assemble a new vector from dataframe
